    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Yeah, that was the point of #18695, to raise when the user passes invalid arguments. `x` and `y` are supposed to be single labels or positions. Passing `x` and `y` sends the code down a path that's expecting all the other kwargs to deal with single values, not multiple.\r\n\r\nIf you want to plot multiple, I'd recommend `df.set_index('i')[['b', 'a']].plot.bar(stacked=True)`. "
